        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Zorlak</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Yes, there was a post here a while back about how to get into the tower.  I have no longer have a link to it so i will give you  what I remember and what I have done sucessfully.</P><P>Step 1: The Jump<BR>At a minimum have these spells memorized and refreshed: (Quivering veil, Harmshield, Feign death). Buff shielding, manaskin, and DMF. Place your pointer over harmshield or get finger over harmshield hotkey. Say a prayer to bertoxxulous. Run into the hole...Before zonning, and while u fall it helps to head in the direction of the tunnel you will enter once u enter the hole...sorta by the lake. (If you are not familiar with the area at the bottom of the hole study a map first. It isnt complicated so dont sweat it).  As SOON as you zone hit that harmshield key and for god's sake do not make any lateral movements which would cause an interupt and a big splat. O and by the way...if master yael is up you will die.  But that has never happened to me.</P><P>Congratulations u are in the hole...now... something is allready aggro on you...and by the way you need SOW, jboots, or runspeed3 to do this.  Head immeditely for tunnel and haul ass though the tunnel. After harmshield has faded you may wish to go ahead and FD...I dont have a prescirbed way or time when I FD...I do it different every time...but I usually FD midway at somepoint to keep the number of things chasing me down to a minimum. And i dont have to tell u...take special precautions if you have aggroed a caster...If u fail FD within the tunnel keep running or use your quivering. you gotta make that call....but ultimately...use your skillz and get all the way through the tunnel...(and on a side note...CoS isnt gonna help, they see invis). Once you emerge from the tunnel you are in an open area. Take a sharp left and stay along that same wall the tunnel mouth is in maybe 10 to 20 feet from the mouth of the tunnel...and then FD there..../quit out to clear aggro. When you come back if you have your back to the wall you will see the undead tower to your left and ahead a little.  You are in a safe spot on that wall.  Invis undead and enter the tower...it is yours now...and I can guarantee you will not have to do a camp check. the tower is 100 percent safe if u have invise undead up...this includes the courtyards and the crypt/basement beneath it.  So feel free to explore the area before trying anything. Take note of where mobs wander.  If you wanna play around with dire you will need to go to the crypt/basement.  it isnt a hard area to get a pet...just ST a dark blue one and dire.  Beware of some pathing issues that can cause a pet to poof in the very back room. A Wanderer (54ish sk) wanders that area so watch out for him and time your moves accordingly.  Personally I dont like using dire in that area...the exp is marginal compared to the top with a regular pet and it can be quite dangerous...But...I guess since i am giving info on this i will give it all...If u are feeling brave there are two mobs that I was able to take down using a DC pet in the area. One is the keeper of the tombs (7 day spawn) which drops a very key item for the fiery defender epic.  He Harmtouches, has a pet, and hits for 220 and has an assload of hps.  Couple of hints...clear inside and wanderer and pull to the inside of the crypt..dont attempt to fight in courtyard. also...pull with slow...if he resists it u better land the next one or you are probably dead or must FD.  Shadowbond the your pet every time it refreshes. If you gain aggro from the start try to loose it with quivering and for god sakes start with a manaskin/FH/FM...dont be a cheapo. Continued.......</P><P><BR> </font></td>
      </tr>
      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Zorlak</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> PART2<BR>The other mob is Dartain the lost...he is rare but i dont know spawn time cause i just did this...it is mroe than 4 or 5 hours though i know that...he can be found behind the locked rock wall in the basement...and for all of you that are of the inferior races...to bad you cant do this mob...only a gnome can duck/slither past the wall...HAH! First /pet guard here you DC pet before slithering past. Warning: this mob is 100MR, hits for 155ish, strong regen, lots of hps, but luckily he is a necro and casts alot of resistable spells. I did this after figuring out he was MR...Used funeral pyre, pyrocuror, and ignite bones for damage. then i used manaskin....stepped into melee until skin dropped and then i took a few bubbles of damage...stepped back out of melee vexed an eye cast manaskin again and stepped back into melee...channel another pyre while u are tanking. rinse and repeat....this is the only way to keep your pet alive....this partial tanking method...its a wild way to kill a mob but it works...and i u dont have holgresh beads tinker stalking probes u lazy gnome!</P><P>Exp in the tower: Go up to the top of the tower while invis undead....look around...explore the area...become familar with the wanderers that travel up and down the ramps. Now, find the ghost of kindle.  Get between her and the nearest wall...basically stand with your back to the wall closest to her.  Yes...u will be very close to her but she is actually non aggressive...The revanant on your left is also non-aggressive.  This is the beauty of this one room.  Drop invis but beware that the rev on the right is aggressive...just dont leave that wall or get too close...there aggro range is pretty small so it may seem like its not safe but it is.  I bind at this locastion and break the tower from here. bring up pet and kill the rev on your right...slow is important. snare is important.  The bastards can be quite resistant at times so i have engulfling darkness up alot as a back up if epic is resisted twice i start doing the fast casting spell engulfing darkness.  I recommend keeping disease resist up since they are necros and cast insidious retro...and it actualy lands sometimes. but not often..ignite blood will land on you and your pet most of the time unless u have uber resists i guess. Evertyhign else i resist 99 percent of the time.  Once you kill one on your right kill one on your left then kill ghost of kindle.  Ghost of kindle is a cleric and can CH...when i kill her i memorize ST to interupt her casting...but if she gets a CH off i dont freak out...she does realatively low damage slowed and i just bring her down to low health again.  After this room you gotta move to get more mobs...beware, the room outside of this room has some MAJOR MAJOR pathing issues...thankfully our pets no longer cause aggro becuase it is not uncommon for the pet to haul ass into another mob filled room...dont worry...i know it is instinct to flip out at the sight of this..but i promise..it will not cuase aggro...anyhow...the room outside of first room has one mob and possible wanderer...try to keep it in the corner it spawns in to be safe...and if pet doesnt seem like it is going to attack mob dont worry...it is fubar pathign and it will eventually warp to the mob.  After i kill this mob i just work my way down the tower stairs and kill all the mobs along the way...just watch out for wanderers...i just kill them fast and handle wanderers if they come...once it is broken it is much less of a problem...anyhow...all said and done i am able to kill 7 of these mobs in a 15 minute cycle...if evertything goes right.  Sometimes i have to feign death and sometimes feign doesnt work because i fucked up the timing and they cast on my feigned....at any rate i think u will find most of the problems are from pathing, and that once u get it figured out it is worth it.  after all killing 7 mobs that are level 49-54 in a +25% exp zone every 15 minutes with pets no longer sharing exp can be quite rewarding...There you have it folks. </P><P>Enough details xzzy or do you need two forms of ID a screenshot and my mothers maiden name? =p</P><P><img src="http://ourworld.cs.com/bgrmail/Final_zor_sig.bmp" border=0></P><P></P><P>Edited by - Zorlak on 08/06/2002  01:09:18</font></td>
